# Delivery Note & Invoice Issuance System (Microsoft Access)

A Microsoft Access-based Delivery Note and Invoice issuance system designed for small to medium-sized businesses (SMBs).
It features input efficiency (autocomplete) and historical data preservation (denormalization), optimized for printing on B5 paper.

## ðŸ“‹ Features

* **Input Assistance**: Displays candidates by simply typing the "reading" of customer or product names, and auto-completes addresses and unit prices.
* **Historical Data Preservation**: Designed to preserve past slip data (information at the time of issuance) even if master data (addresses or prices) changes in the future.
* **B5 Printing Support**: Optimized for B5 paper (vertical), sequentially outputting a Delivery Note followed by an Invoice.

## ðŸ›  Tech Stack / Environment

* **Platform**: Microsoft Access (Office 365 / 2019 or later recommended)
* **Language**: VBA (minimal event control), Access Macro
* **File Format**: `.accdb`

---

## ðŸ’¾ Database Structure (Schema & ER Diagram)

This system follows a typical "Header-Detail" relational database structure but includes **intentionally denormalized fields** to preserve historical data integrity.

### ER Diagram (Mermaid)

```mermaid
erDiagram
    T_SALES ||--|{ T_SALES_DETAIL : "One-to-Many"
    T_CUSTOMER ||--|{ T_SALES : "Lookup"
    T_ITEM ||--|{ T_SALES_DETAIL : "Lookup"

    T_SALES {
        long SalesID PK "AutoNumber"
        long CustomerID FK "Reference Only"
        date SalesDate
        string DeliveryName_Saved "History Kept"
        string AddressInfo_Saved "History Kept"
    }

    T_SALES_DETAIL {
        long SalesDetailID PK "AutoNumber"
        long SalesID FK
        long ItemID FK "Reference Only"
        string ItemName_Saved "History Kept"
        currency UnitPrice_Saved "History Kept"
        int Quantity
    }
